# Dockerfile.render-specific ignore file. BuildKit prefers <dockerfile>.dockerignore
# over the shared .dockerignore when building with `-f Dockerfile.render` -- this lets
# this build keep models/ and data/ visible (it deliberately BAKES specific artifacts
# into the image, since Render's free tier has no persistent disk) while the shared
# .dockerignore keeps excluding them entirely for Dockerfile.api (which relies on
# docker-compose volume mounts instead and must NOT bake them in). See docs/DEPLOYMENT.md.

.env
.env.*

notebooks/
src/dashboard/
docs/
requirements.txt
requirements-dev.txt
.claude
.git
.github

# Not COPYed by Dockerfile.render -- excluded here only to keep the upload context
# small, not for correctness (explicit COPYs below would skip them regardless).
models/delay/
models/fallback/
models/cache/
data/processed/shards/
data/processed/chroma_kb/
data/raw/
data/synthetic/
logs/

# Per-station ticket anomaly model (Phase 2 drill-down) -- 196MB, well past GitHub's
# 100MB hard limit and not part of the exposed ENABLED_MODULES=anomaly,ticket_anomaly
# surface (decision 2026-07-12: keep it for local/dashboard use, don't ship it to the
# free-tier image). /api/ticket-anomaly-stations already degrades gracefully to an
# empty result when this directory is absent -- no code change needed for this to be
# safe to exclude.
models/ticket_anomaly/stations/

# Full dev reference DB (114MB, includes the per-arret ticket tables the drill-down
# above needs) -- NOT git-tracked (see .gitignore) or COPYed here. The image instead
# gets winicari_reference_slim.db (~57MB, same schema minus tickets_station_daily/
# tickets_station_trip_daily), renamed to the expected path in the COPY step below.
data/reference/winicari_reference.db

# foundation_arrivals_full.parquet -- not COPYed by Dockerfile.render (decision
# 2026-07-13, see the note there): still OOM'd at 512Mi even after a 5x in-memory
# shrink, and the endpoints that are actually exposed (anomaly-history,
# ticket-anomaly-*) read the precomputed trips_scored.parquet/days_scored.parquet
# instead, not this file. Excluded here for build-context size, not correctness.
data/processed/foundation_arrivals_full.parquet

__pycache__/
*.pyc
.ipynb_checkpoints/
.pytest_cache/
